entry.title: Add naive implementation of `beginWebGPUAccess`.
entry.content:
Explainer:

https://github.com/fserb/canvas2D/blob/master/spec/webgpu.md



This API converts a canvas' currently-displayed image to a

GPUTexture which can be used by WebGPU. At present, the current

implementation uses Snapshot(), which always clones the image.

An ideal design would avoid this copy, but this gives us a

starting point to iterate from.



We do not yet have any guards against continuing to use the

Canvas2D APIs after calling `beginWebGPUAccess`. This is safe

because we don't actually steal the existing texture away from

the canvas; it still has its own storage, distinct from the WebGPU

texture. Once `endWebGPUAccess` is implemented, it is expected

that this would clobber any canvas changes that might have

occurred during WebGPU access (as the canvas texture would be

replaced by the GPUTexture from WebGPU).

As discussed in https://issues.chromium.org/issues/40065516#comment32,

Chromium was always setting the AutomationId to an empty string even

when no value was provided. While this respects the UIA documentation,

it was causing issues with the native UIA enablement for some

customers that were checking whether this value was set or not.



The UIA bridge was not doing the right thing by not setting it to an explicitly empty string when not provided, and customers started

relying on this bug as if it was a feature.



Instead of always settings an empty string as value, we now set the

document node's AutomationId to "RootWebArea". This should fix their

issue, while still respecting the documentation.

entry.title: Prepare to convert SBThreatType to an enum class in /chrome/browser/apps/guest_view
entry.content:
It's somewhat difficult to log an SBThreatType as an UMA histogram since

we don't have a kMaxValue. We can't simply add a kMaxValue because

SBThreatType is an enum instead of enum class, and we'd be exposing a

constant safe_browsing::kMaxValue. This CL prepares to convert

SBThreatType to an enum class in /chrome/browser/apps/guest_view.



That requires two changes:



- SBThreatType is no longer implicitly convertible to int, so we will

need a few static casts



- SBThreatType values are now in the namespace

safe_browsing::SBThreatType instead of just safe_browsing. In some

places this is fixed by adding the new namespace, and in some places

with a "using enum" declaration. We can't just add a "using enum" for

all usages of SBThreatType because "using enum" would declare a

constant kMaxValue. So "using enum" is only used when many

SBThreatType constants are used, and in as narrow a scope as possible.



This CL was uploaded by git cl split.

entry.title: Reland "[DIPS] Add ChromeDriver support for Bounce Tracking Mitigations"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit 37078af2fda407a920e73ab809cc3e0411e9a536



Most importantly, https://crrev.com/c/5374999/ fixed a race

condition that stopped Bounce Tracking Mitigations from classifying

bounces as stateful if cookie accesses by the bouncing site/page

were reported after the navigation to the landing page had already

started.



This CL improves upon the original by restructuring the python

integration test for the RunBounceTrackingMitigations command to use

distinct pages for each stage of the bounce flow, rather than reusing

the initial page. This ensures a stateful bounce actually occurs and

is recorded before the command is executed.



Additionally, the test is added to the browser specific filter for

chrome-headless-shell, since the python integration tests are now also

run against chrome-headless-shell and Bounce Tracking Mitigations is

implemented in //chrome.

entry.title: Allow using `cargo vet` in offline mode (`--locked --frozen`).
entry.content:
In the future we want `cargo vet` to be used by

`third_party/rust/PRESUBMIT.py` and when used in this mode, we want

`cargo vet` to be somewhat hermetic. This CL helps with that by

ensuring that `--locked --frozen` switches work when used as follows:



```

$ tools/crates/run_cargo_vet.py check \

--locked --frozen \

--no-minimize-exemptions --no-registry-suggestions \

--output-format=json

{

"conclusion": "success",

"vetted_fully": [

{

"name": "aho-corasick",

"version": "1.1.2"

},

...

```



The CL achieves the above by:



* Reintroducing a pre-populated `imports.lock` file.

- Having this in the repo means that code reviews will explicitly

include information about newly imported audits.

- Note that (per https://github.com/mozilla/cargo-vet/issues/272)

`imports.lock` should hopefully see minimal churn, because it

should only cover imports that are actually used.

- In a sense, this CL reverts/reconsiders `imports.lock`-related parts

of https://crrev.com/c/5368308

* Tweaking `vet_config.toml.hbs` to produce `config.toml` with the exact

formatting expected by `cargo vet`.

- This has some downsides - e.g. we loose the

'@generated by tools/crates/gnrt vendor. Do not edit.' comment.

- This is necessary because even formatting-only discrepancies trigger

an error in `--locked` mode: "A file in the store is not correctly

formatted [...] run `cargo vet` without --locked to reformat files

in the store"

- This is somewhat related to

https://github.com/mozilla/cargo-vet/issues/589

- In a sense, this CL makes obsolete the `config.toml`-related parts

of https://crrev.com/c/5368308. OTOH, detecting changes to

`config.toml` (including a comments-only change) is not harmful, so

let's leave the detection logic in place (in `run_cargo_vet.py).

entry.title: gpu: IOSurface GL synchronization fixes
entry.content:
Make the following changes to IOSurface GL synchronization:



1) IOSurface GL EndAccess should enqueue a shared event and mark the

display as having pending commands even if it's readonly access since

we want it to end up in the non-exclusive events list that's used to

synchronize future read-write access.



2) Skip ReleaseTexImage and glFlush for non-Swiftshader GL access, and

instead rely on eglWaitUntilWorkScheduledANGLE which works for both

ANGLE Metal (calls Metal waitUntilScheduled) and OpenGL (calls flush

on each context). Swiftshader still needs the ReleaseTexImage call

so that it can copy from its internal texture to the IOSurface.



3) Make ReadbackToMemory and UploadToMemory also wait for Dawn and ANGLE

work to be scheduled so that the DawnFallbackImageRepresentation path

for Dawn on Vulkan-Swiftshader works correctly.



4) Minor readability improvements with respect to checking the EGLState

bind_pending and egl_surfaces_.

entry.title: Run GetPlatformTimeZone on worker thread to avoid jank on Windows
entry.content:
On Windows, the Timezone changes are detected by listening to

WM_TIMECHANGE event. Whenever the time change event (WM_TIMECHANGE) is

received, a call is made to windows API ::GetTimeZoneInformation to get

the current time zone. If the current time zone differs from the

previously cached time zone, then the notification is sent to the

observers of TimeZoneMonitor.



::GetTimeZoneInformation which is called from within GetPlatformTimeZone

method is causing jank in Browser Process Main UI thread (blocking

BrowserProcess UI thread on an avg for ~1.5 seconds).



The fix here is to execute GetPlatformTimeZone as a task on worker

thread instead on UI thread. The time zone value (returned from this

worker thread task) is passed to another task which resumes execution

on the UI thread to notify time zone change to the observers of

TimeZoneMonitor if the recent and previous time zone are different.

entry.content:

"--test" to put into the "test" named arg. This has some incorrect

So this fixes that by changing the "-t" arg from accepting N vals

after it, to only accepting one, but allowing "-t" to be repeated.

This fixes the above error.

entry.title: [UNO] Move password to account store after promo sign in
entry.content:
This CL implements the functionality to move the password to the

account store after a successful sign in event from the password sign in promo.



- If the user is already signed in on the web, the password is moved

immediately after the sign in.

- If the user does not have an account yet, the

`AutofillSigninPromoTabHelper` will listen for sign in events

with the correct access point for 50 minutes and move the password

once this there was a sign in.

- If the account is in a "sign in paused" state (e.g. signed into

Chrome, signed out from the web), the password will be uploaded to

the account store directly after successful verification and does not

need to be moved (addressed in b:329811644).

entry.title: [flex] Sync ContentBlockSizeFunc with BlockNode::ComputeMinMaxSizes
entry.content:
Previously when computing the flex base size we'd explicitly handle

transferred sizes. There isn't a need to do this, instead we can

rely on determining the content-size (for both axes).



The primary logic change is to harmonize ContentBlockSizeFunc with how

content sizes work in BlockNode::ComputeMinMaxSizes.



If we have an aspect-ratio - try and resolve our inline-size, and if

definite use that as the content size.



Otherwise use the intrinsic size - clamped by the transferred min/max

sizes.



This patch allows us to remove a bunch of indirect dependencies on

InlineLengthUnresolvable/BlockLengthUnresolvable.
